sentences: Noel Paul Stookey (born December 30, 1937) is an American singer-songwriter.
His family moved to Birmingham, Michigan, when he was 12 years old, and he graduated from Birmingham High School (now Seaholm High School) in 1955.
Stookey married Elizabeth "Betty" Bannard in 1963 and they have three daughters.

After raising their family in Blue Hill, Maine, the couple lived for several years in Massachusetts while Betty served as the Northfield Mount Hermon School chaplain, and in 2005, they returned to Maine.
